Recently, I have ventured into graph theory, addressing the challenge of generating structurally diverse graphs. I have defined measures of diversity and proposed various algorithms, including genetic and neural generative models, to optimize these measures. This work not only enhances our understanding of graph properties but also provides valuable tools for testing graph algorithms and their neural approximations.

