roposal attached. If possible, could you provide your feedback by [deadline]? Any specific comments on the clarity, feasibility, and completeness of the proposal would be particularly helpful.\n\nThank you very much for your time and assistance.\n\nBest regards,  \n[Your Name]  \n[Your Contact Information]\n\n### Next Task\n\nAfter sharing the draft proposal with peers or mentors, the next task will be to **incorporate the feedback** received. This involves:\n\n1. **Reviewing Feedback:**\n   - Carefully read through all the feedback provided by the reviewers.\n   - Identify common themes and specific suggestions.\n\n2. **Revising the Proposal:**\n   - Make necessary revisions based on the feedback.\n   - Address any concerns or suggestions raised by the reviewers.\n\n3. **Iterating:**\n   - If needed, share the revised proposal with the reviewers for further feedback.\n   - Repeat the process until the proposal is satisfactory.\n\nBy following these steps, you can ensure that the research proposal is well-refined and ready for submission or presentation.", 'agent3': 'Given the current state of the research proposal refinement process, the next logical step is to integrate the insights and potential collaboration from Agent1, particularly focusing on the graph theory aspects of the research. Here’s a structured plan for the next task:\n\n### Next Task: Integrate Insights from Agent1 and Develop Detailed Methodology\n\n**Objective:** Incorporate insights from Agent1 on graph theory and develop a detailed methodology for extending the Vendi Score to different ML domains and developing methods for automated similarity function selection.\n\n**Steps:**\n\n1. **Review Insights from Agent1:**\n   - Review any insights or suggestions provided by Agent1 regarding the graph theory aspects of the research.\n   - Identify any specific methodologies or techniques suggested for extending the Vendi Score to graph-based ML domains.\n\n2. **Select Key Areas:**\n   - Focus on extendi